annotation.plain:
Triple entendre:


Genesis 5 talks about how rain fell on the earth for forty days and for forty nights. Rain symbolizes crying in many cases;
Some people use 40 days and 40 nights as a healing process;
40 days and 40 nights is the length of lent.

The lyric “cruel to be kind” was likely inspired by a line from Shakespeare’s Hamlet

I must be cruel only to be kind;
Thus bad begins, and worse remains behind.
